Hi Rob,

I answered that question in my last post. You can't register a  
vehicle in Ontario unless it has paperwork that has preceded its  
arrival at customs. This paperwork can only be processed with the  
vehicle present at the border crossing.

On 16-Oct-05, at 2:16 PM, Rob wrote:

> Any reason you couldn't you get the title, register it at 'home'  
> before you left and arrive with the 'home' licence plate and just  
> take it home?


